  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nVersion: 1.9.10-unstable\r\nGit Commit: 3e97b04a3df8a175b7cc61ae8f6f7e0d40f5cd4b\r\nGit Commit Date: 20200116\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nProtocol Versions: [64 63]\r\nGo Version: go1.11.13\r\nOperating System: darwin\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nNon-local, non-executable transactions held in txpool.queue should be discarded after the time specififed by `--txpool.lifetime` has passed (similar to the behaviour for pending transactions).\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nNon-local, non-executable transactions are removed from txpool.queue on the next tick of the `evictionInterval` timer, which ticks every minute.\r\nThis basically means that any non-local transaction with a future nonce will get deleted, if it doesn't quickly become eligible for execution.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n- Run geth with `--txpool.nolocals`, to simulate non-local transactions.\r\n- Submit a transaction with a future nonce, so that it sits in txpool.queue.\r\n- When the next tick occurs (within one minute), the transaction will be deleted from the queue.\r\n\r\nLooking into this issue, I can see that transactions are removed from the queue by the following code in tx_pool.go:\r\n```\r\nif time.Since(pool.beats[addr]) > pool.config.Lifetime {\r\n\tfor _, tx := range pool.queue[addr].Flatten() {\r\n\t\tpool.removeTx(tx.Hash(), true)\r\n\t}\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe problem is that pool.beats[addr] is not being initialised for non-executable transactions.\r\nThe code to initialise pool.beats[] was added in [promoteTx()](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/core/tx_pool.go#L728) for executable transactions as part of [PR #2742](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/pull/2742).\r\nHowever, that code should also have been added for non-executables in [enqueueTx()](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/core/tx_pool.go#L652).\r\n",
